text: Best 辣子鸡, will travel from Orchard to Tampines for it. Also the 烤鱼, always fresh and full of other ingredients! Uncle is super friendly too.

Food and service is good!! The chef is very nice and friendly been patronising for a year now! And, I like how they don't have a min. amount charge for the Mala so you do not have to order a lot just to meet the min. amount requirement that most Mala stalls put in place! Can't say much about atmosphere as it's located in a coffee shop.
I like to tabao and hv it at my comfort home. One of the best mala xiang guo in tampines. I like their 回锅肉饭，cheap at 6 dollar, delicious and filling! Then i add on my own cucumber, perfect lunch
Delicious 酸菜鱼 served in a huge bowl, very appetizing and fish slices are tender and fresh.
Avoid during lunch and dinner times. Will have to wait for prolonged time as owner prior China customers
